Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.28,0:00:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I've talked to Dr. Hawkins, and I can tell you he's in rare form.\NSo put your hands together and welcome again our mentor and teacher, Dr. David Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.64,0:01:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see, according to the schedule, what is today called?\NQuestions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditional dialogue between teachers and students.\NAnd that's what we'll do today primarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.96,0:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We, of course, have new slides, which we promise not to subject you to today.\NExciting new developments, because the consciousness research just keeps pulling up amazing information
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it all correlates is rather staggering.\NSo I'll control myself and try not to show you a new slide that's just mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.01,0:02:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We might show them one.\NWe might show them one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I'm holding in mind is okay to show them.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're going to do it a little differently.\NWe'll go up here and we're going to discuss things in greater detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.52,0:02:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All the questions that, of course, now wonderful season.\NAll these flowers seem to indicate something coming up in a couple of weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which we will avoid mentioning in public, of course.\NSort of a special day that comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One of a number of special days.\NActually, we're the only secular spiritual group on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mentioned no religion.\NIf you stick to the Rhapsody of the Soul stunningly, it doesn't represent any particular religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't represent any school.\NIt teaches stunningly, starkly, totality of all, the source of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.38,0:04:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Its nature shines forth from all that exists and makes it difficult to function in the world,\Nso we won't talk about it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the lecture will come to an end.\NSo it's not necessary to get caught in the trappings of tradition
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with all of the incrustation that has occurred to it over the years.\NIt starts out as some kind of a purity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.17,0:04:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,radiating forth from someone who has realized the presence of God is the source of all existence,\Nand then it becomes institutionalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And within the institutionalization, then it becomes encrusted and rigid.\NSultifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then people are brought up in it as children,\Nand they become antagonistic to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.07,0:05:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't want to hear about it again,\Nand become champions of the opposite of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.60,0:05:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,having been disillusioned or suffered some kind of discomfort\Ndue to the way in which it was presented to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They avoid it altogether.\NAnd therefore, we can say truthfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we are the only secular spiritual group that I know of.\NTruth needs no external authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth speaks for itself.\NThe devotion to truth is the devotion to the essence of the source of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which in some quarters and historically has been called God.\NI agree with the Buddha it's better not to mention such a word,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has become imbued with so many meanings.\NSo many meanings that there's opposition to its use in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.86,0:06:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so many meanings that there's opposition to its use in.\NBecause it seems to those people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.18,0:06:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that it represents some kind of an oppression or loss of freedom.\NSo that which is the true source of freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.86,0:06:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes pictured as the enemy of freedom.\NAnd therefore, I can understand how they think and feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of the patients I've had\Nwho were the most rigidly opposed to any kind of religion or spiritual teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.06,0:06:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,had traditional religious upbringing,\Nand so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say I, come to think of it,\NI became an atheist myself, I forgot about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.81,0:07:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, yeah.\NThat's because religion didn't really differentiate between the ego and the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And, blame God for really for that which is the production of the ego\Nwhich is what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've told you I was extremely religious as a boy, scrupulous.\NI was a boy soprano,
