Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.07,0:48:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She hates her.\NSo we respect our animal
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.03,0:48:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution. We stop\Nglorifying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.03,0:48:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If the universe is created by divinity\Nthen that's how it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.03,0:48:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,unfolded.\NWe are serving some purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.25,0:48:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to connect this evolutionary\Nline with
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.28,0:48:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a life that\Ntakes over on a non-physical
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.05,0:48:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,level.\NThe devotion to truth then.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.42,0:48:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is that the ego\Nis nothing but one's biologic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.61,0:48:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ancestry.\NIt lives on in the very
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.28,0:48:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,structure and anatomy\Nof the human brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.92,0:48:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Without it you wouldn't even be alive.\NSo you can give it credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.01,0:49:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for good old ego\NI wouldn't be standing here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.82,0:49:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However,\Nthe spiritual energy which also
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.15,0:49:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,surrounds humanity\Nbegins to pull us even beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.15,0:49:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to say,\Nisn't there something more?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.80,0:49:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there something better?\NBut I want you to be aware
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.80,0:49:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ego is not\Nadhering to any religion whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.98,0:49:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And never even mentioning it.\NNot necessary to mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.55,0:49:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As you let go now\Nthat this is the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.94,0:49:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,if you didn't understand anything about the ego\Nand I just told you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.94,0:49:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind is not at the service\Nto the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.94,0:49:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become a student of your own mind\Nand get a little notebook
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.94,0:49:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and you notice what your animal did today\Nwhat it did today
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.98,0:49:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you become\Na psychologist by here
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.98,0:50:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,being a student of your own nature\Nhow it shines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.01,0:50:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it shines forth in everyone.\NSo it doesn't have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.01,0:50:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,secret, it doesn't have to be mystical\Nit doesn't have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.42,0:50:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,couched in foreign languages\Nyou don't have to pull it out of antiquity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.42,0:50:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's observable\Nrediscoverable right now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.88,0:50:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the immediate present.\NBegin to own it for what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.61,0:50:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin surrendering it.\NAnd as you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.80,0:50:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as it comes up\Nyou can forgive it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.11,0:50:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you can let it go\Nyou can let go wanting to control it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.76,0:50:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there are all the mechanisms\Nthat all the various schools and workshops
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.11,0:50:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,teach various mechanisms\Nmeditation and contemplation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.84,0:50:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one that I\Nrecommend because
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.84,0:50:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unstoppable\Nis contemplation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.19,0:51:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation you see\Nyou gotta sort of take yourself out of it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.19,0:51:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and go someplace\Nlike it and give yourself tendinitis
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.40,0:51:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuff\Nyou know every orthopedist says
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.67,0:51:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,practicing meditation eh?\Nknees twisted up
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.86,0:51:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your back all warped out\Nso people will take a course
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.51,0:51:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,on meditation become intensely involved\Nin a weekend workshop
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.51,0:51:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and be with some teachers\Netc and then
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.59,0:51:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you visit them again in Chicago three years later\Nand they've given it up long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.59,0:51:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,why is that? Because\Nyou gotta take time out from real life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.59,0:51:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say real life\Nto do this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.61,0:51:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just don't have time to do that\Nfor the same reason you gave up playing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.61,0:51:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Parcheesi years ago\Nyou just haven't got time to get out
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.67,0:51:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the game board and go someplace\Nand say you wanna play Parcheesi
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.76,0:52:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,eh? Chinese marbles\Nor whatever it was
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.61,0:52:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna say scruple\Nscrapple what was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.71,0:52:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in my childhood\Nit was called scruple not scrapple
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.65,0:52:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,scruples\Nscrupulous
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.51,0:52:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,scrapless\Nso we don't have time to take out
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.78,0:52:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so we skip it\Ntherefore a contemplative way
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.03,0:52:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of being in the world\Nwhen you get to consciousness level 500
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.51,0:52:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this happens anyway\None just begins
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.71,0:52:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to appreciate more and more\Nthe beauty of life
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.71,0:52:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,one becomes sensitized to beauty\Nand beauty itself is one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.71,0:52:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,pathways to God\Nthe virtue of one's spiritual commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.32,0:52:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore\Nyou open doors
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.00,0:53:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential doors\Nand the progression of experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.00,0:53:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that would not have occurred\Nhad you not made that commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.11,0:53:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to be spiritually committed\Nis to automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.11,0:53:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,bring into your presence\Ninto your existence
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.11,0:53:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,into your experience of your own existence\Nthings sequencing
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.30,0:53:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves\Nin a way that would not have happened otherwise
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.50,0:53:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,doors open\Nthat wouldn't have opened
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.50,0:53:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you say I don't know\Njust I got there and the door opened
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.82,0:53:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nwhat is it a miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.65,0:53:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,call it miracles\Nbut that again is going in the other direction
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.65,0:53:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,no\Nit isn't a miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.75,0:53:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what's normal\Nthat's reality for a spiritually committed person
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.78,0:53:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,things should work out\None should uncover new sources of joy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.07,0:53:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all part and parcel\Ntherefore spiritual commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.15,0:54:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,pulls into you\Na field
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.19,0:54:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the field then begins to support you\Nit's not you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.36,0:54:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not miracles\Nit's nothing special
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.36,0:54:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the automatic consequence of the field\Nan ocean without salt
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.11,0:54:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,has different buoyancy\Nthan an ocean with salt
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.25,0:54:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,all you've done is add tremendous salt\Nand now you're more buoyant than you were before
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.25,0:54:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so you float higher\Nas a consequence of your spiritual commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.82,0:54:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course you think differently\Nyou see things differently
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.82,0:54:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because spiritual commitment\Nautomatically changes brain function
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.01,0:54:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it changes brain function\Nit automatically creates an etheric brain
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.11,0:54:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one now has an instrument\Nthrough which all experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.15,0:54:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,filtered or processed\Nwhich is not present
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.15,0:54:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo Dragon doesn't have an etheric brain\Nhe doesn't really worry about things
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.03,0:55:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lucky from a certain viewpoint right\Nlucky Komodo Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.28,0:55:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate and give reverence\Nto our own spiritual nature
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.28,0:55:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have owned it\Nand acknowledged it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.11,0:55:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and in so doing\Nwe have benefited all of mankind forever
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.11,0:55:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a group like this\Nby merely owning
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.76,0:55:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of your own spiritual power\Nand truth
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.30,0:55:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,changes the consciousness of mankind\Nchanges the consciousness of mankind forever
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.53,0:55:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,changes the consciousness of mankind forever\Nnot disconnected from it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.57,0:55:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are the consciousness\Nthe infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.15,0:55:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is here present\Nwithin all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.30,0:55:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we move our spiritual commitment\Nto the field
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.82,0:56:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the field itself becomes more powerfully influential\Nin all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.11,0:56:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with each other\Nbecause of each and every one of us
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.42,0:56:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,each and every one of us benefits\NI benefit by you sitting right there
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.42,0:56:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I benefit by you\Nevery single person here
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.46,0:56:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we all enormously radiate\Nenormous power
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.46,0:56:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to each other\Nwhich I never speak of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.00,0:56:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but today I thought I would\Nthat's a fact
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.48,0:56:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we are all moving along\Nnot just as a consequence of our
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.48,0:56:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,being so wonderful ourselves\Nbut the fact that we are surrounded by people
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.48,0:56:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who are wonderful\Nand we are included in their field
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.84,0:56:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so all of life benefits\Nand by our commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.40,0:56:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and we automatically bring the miraculous\Ninto our life
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.40,0:56:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as the everyday\Nthings
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.76,0:56:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when other people drop a button\Nfrom the bureau
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.44,0:57:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't find it\Nand you say Holy Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.92,0:57:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to have that button\Nyou find it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.01,0:57:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you think everybody does that\Nno they don't
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.01,0:57:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't find the button\Nif it wasn't for the Holy Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.55,0:57:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we would never find our cat\Nhe keeps getting lost
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.55,0:57:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we have staff in and out\Nand the office is attached to the house
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.55,0:57:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so we have to have that button\Nthus far
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.40,0:57:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy Spirit has answered every prayer\NI ask God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.40,0:57:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,where is the kitty\Nand the next thing you move over
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.51,0:57:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and there underneath the pillow\Na little tail sticking out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.30,0:57:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is the kitty\NI just want us to really appreciate ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.82,0:58:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for this holiday season\Nand it should be nameless of course
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.53,0:58:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because this lecture could be heard by others\Nin this bleep season
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.96,0:58:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which is\Nthe day of the rising
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.05,0:58:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it just increases our awareness\Nof the presence of love
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.05,0:58:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as a prevailing quality\Nof all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.05,0:58:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see it in all that exists\Nit appears as beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.44,0:58:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,stillness\Nsilence
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.19,0:58:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going over the mountain\Nyesterday the snow
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.76,0:58:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the divinity\Nyou just see the divinity of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.80,0:59:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing itself as existence\Nin that beauty of this incredible form
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.42,0:59:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when we go out\Ncoming to your restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.42,0:59:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin calibrating\NChinese fortune cookies
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.55,0:59:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,did I mention them to you\Nyes or no
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.13,0:59:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,no\Nno
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.13,0:59:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,oh\Nwell I lecture in various places
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.63,0:59:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I guess this was in\Nwhere are we in California
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.50,0:59:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and Пượcка\Nyou know everybody's worrying about truth
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.50,0:59:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say truth is\NIt's just that if you have the capacity to see it, we found that Chinese fortune cookies calibrate around 350.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.17,0:59:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you look at one, for the first time you begin to really look at one,\Nyou'll see something like, a kind thought can change your life forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.78,1:00:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!\NOne kind thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.48,1:00:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate Chinese fortune cookies calibrate at 350.\NA single kind word will keep one warm for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.21,1:00:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, will come to you by mail.\NThis side's in Chinese. I can't read it. Oh, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.86,1:00:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have at your command the wisdom of the ages.\NAs you begin looking at Chinese fortune cookies, we calibrated them generically, they calibrate at 350,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.69,1:00:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which beats a large proportion of the world's\Nliterature and spiritual literature.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.86,1:01:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if you would just read Chinese fortune cookies.\NNow tell him, he said, what should I do to become enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.69,1:01:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, this is what you do.\NCall me in 20 years, tell me how it worked out. To be kind at all times,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.19,1:01:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to be kind at all times towards all of life and all of its expressions.\NDo you need anything more than that? No, because as you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.96,1:01:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to change its occurrence to you.\NAnd what you thought was just a dumb animal, you see, is the radiance of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.26,1:02:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I use that word, the radiance of the source of life.\NOne Chinese fortune cookie, you do it consistently as a way of being is all kind of read anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.94,1:02:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,do anything, go anywhere. You just do that as a way of being in the world.\NSo contemplation is owning a reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.59,1:02:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it alters the way you are. To be kind towards all things,\Ntransforms all of life. Is that what it's saying? To see the truth of it, and it shines for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.19,1:02:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you make it your way of life.\NMake it your way of life. And as you do that, everything around you begins to get transformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.98,1:02:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything around you seems to change.\NSo that is our wish. That's my present to you for this coming holiday season.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.84,1:03:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Chinese fortune cookie, fortune, which has the power to transform all of life.\NSo we'll take a break and then we'll just do questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.51,1:03:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't run a fortune cookie.\NDifferent format today, we set up everything differently, the microphones, the cameras.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.05,1:04:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll have people come up and sit here and we can have a dialogue, discuss things.\NAlso, we have questions that are already presented on cards.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.80,1:04:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try to answer them.\NWe'll try to answer everything as best we can, or at least I'll give you my response to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.94,1:04:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My response to it, which may not be the answer that you're looking for.\NBut I'll give you the response.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.63,1:04:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them ask technical questions, the answer to which I really don't know.\NBut they're not too relevant anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.59,1:04:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try to sort out the relevant from the irrelevant.\NSee, the mind likes to think in terms of content.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.23,1:04:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the intellect,\Nwhich is in the 400s, with the prevailing energy, which brings us all here,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.90,1:05:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is because we're all articulate, we all read, we follow reason and logic.\NAnd we pretty much mastered, mastered in the operational sense, the mind and the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.13,1:05:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're interested in what is beyond that.\NThe mind and the intellect will examine how it sort of developed over time in the next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.80,1:05:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NWe calibrated all.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.67,1:05:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world.\NEvery contributor to the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.51,1:05:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest intellects that have ever lived.\NBut that'll be next.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.05,1:05:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll track where the intellect can take us.\NSo anyway, the intellect thinks up questions and we'll try to answer them.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.71,1:05:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What can a group like this, this is one of the cards, do to raise the consciousness of mankind?\NAnd as I explained this morning, we've already done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.25,1:05:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha!\NHa!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.65,1:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha!\NThe collective intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.73,1:05:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To raise consciousness.\NThat's not our intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.36,1:06:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we don't all take up spiritual work in order to raise the consciousness level of mankind.\NI mean, it's not your province.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.36,1:06:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave that for the Avatar.\NThat's why the Avatar is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.30,1:06:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's his responsibility.\NYou worry about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.23,1:06:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcend the level of the hippopotamus.\NTo be kindly and loving towards all things.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.90,1:06:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To follow that Chinese fortune cookie will take you the whole way.\NBecause...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.48,1:06:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one opens the door to the next revelation.\NAnd the next revelation, you move from that level and that takes you to the next revolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.17,1:06:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See, once you begin opening the doors, they open up their own.\NAnd when you do that, you collapse the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.30,1:06:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a question, what does that mean, collapse the wave function?\NThere, on the internet, Henry Stapp, S-T-A-P-P, professor out of Berkeley, advanced theoretical
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.65,1:06:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,physics.\NDoes about as good a job.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.73,1:07:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He explained it, you know, from the potentiality, which is the Schrodinger equations, time dependent\Nand time independent, then arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.59,1:07:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the state of the universe.\NThat is the state of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.11,1:07:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Any condition of the universe is obviously potentially the source of the next stage,\Nis it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.59,1:07:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that there I'm here, I can decipher this with the Schrodinger equations, it now\Nhas a potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.07,1:07:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By exercise.\NBy exercise of the Heisenberg principle of observation, and especially that of intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.40,1:07:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I now potentiate the potential to an actuality.\NNow I have a new state of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.48,1:07:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've collapsed the wave function.\NAnd now, to mathematically discover what's happened to my arm, you need the Dirac equations.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.63,1:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All that happens through the von Neumann process, process one and process two.\NAnd if you're interested in that, read it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.88,1:08:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very interesting stuff.\NVery interesting stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.11,1:08:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need it, but it's interesting.\NHere, I'm telling you how to transcend mind, and now I'm giving you all this mind fodder.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.88,1:08:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving me a guilt panic thing here.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.27,1:08:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the reason I like to bring those things in is because you don't have to desert intelligence.\NYou see, one objection of the atheist is he has to transcend confirmable, verifiable truth
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.72,1:08:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to that ooh-la-la stuff, all that ooh-ooh-ooh stuff.\NHe's the director of a big clinic, not too far from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.09,1:08:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And any time many of the staff wanted to bring any kind of spirituality, he'd go,\Nall that ooh-ooh-ooh stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.85,1:09:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all that ooh-ooh-ooh stuff has stopped the greatest intellects of history.\NSir Isaac Newton at 499, Sigmund Freud at 499, Albert Einstein at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.15,1:09:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is a great barrier.\NAnd my job as a teacher is really how to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.35,1:09:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualize things so that the transcendence of the intellect becomes an automatic consequence\Nof the process itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.73,1:09:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the intellect is the great trap.\NVery few people get beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.60,1:09:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember from Calvary, love is the consciousness.\NOnly 4% of the world's population ever gets to the level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.32,1:09:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 4%.\NAnd that's love, which is a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.92,1:09:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're moving from the supposedly objective intellect,\Nthe world of content, and you're moving to the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.15,1:09:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the movement from the describable Newtonian paradigm to the paradigm of spiritual reality\Nmeans you move from the out-there-ness of what you think life is about to the in-here-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.43,1:10:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of pure subjectivity, which is where life is.\NLife ain't out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.86,1:10:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in subjectivity.\NSo we just got a new...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.76,1:10:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,fire from a new conference on science and consciousness and all the intellectuals.\NYou calibrate the level of that particular conference.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.63,1:10:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about 405, 410.\NYou can't take an instrument that calibrates in the 400s and use that to understand a universe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.43,1:10:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that begins at 500.\NIt doesn't dawn on people.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.14,1:10:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a paradigm jump.\NIt's a paradigm problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.55,1:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't use the tools.\NYou can't find ghosts with Geiger counters.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.63,1:10:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it all the time on TV.\NYou know, they've got the Geiger counters, the infrared things, and looking for ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.51,1:10:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the wrong instrument.\NIt's like trying to tell the temperature with a barometer.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.02,1:11:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the barometer is for something different.\NSo you move from the supposed out-there-ness described by Descartes as res externa,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.07,1:11:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called out-there-ness.\NYou move to the source of subjectivity because the intellect is only true to the degree that you're
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.35,1:11:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing it.\NIt's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.80,1:11:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you worship the intellect, you're only doing so because on the subjective, it\Nseems to you, convincing, important, and real.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.59,1:11:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot avoid subjectivity.\NThat's the source of the awareness of divinity within you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.06,1:11:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you look to the content of mind, you'll never find spiritual reality because it's\Nnot in the content of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.18,1:11:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the subjective awareness of experience.\NYou have the emanation of consciousness and divinity shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.26,1:11:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As awareness consciousness.\NAnd then you can say consciousness of what?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.97,1:11:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But the of what?\NThis is what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.53,1:12:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The of what-ness is irrelevant.\NIt's always aware of something.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.69,1:12:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So who cares what the something is?\NThe sense of joy is the sense of joy and it stems from the expression and experience of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.39,1:12:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,its own nature.\NAnd the ultimate source of joy is the awareness of the existence of God as the very source
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.77,1:12:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own life.\NAnd that's the essence of human existence every instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.53,1:12:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't know how I got off that, but somebody asked me a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.60,1:12:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked me the correct question about the collective, you see.\NSo that's what happens when you start off on the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.35,1:12:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up just describing quantum theory.\NThe collapse of the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.53,1:12:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what happens to your mind?\NIt easily grabs you and sucks you in.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.93,1:12:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.06,1:13:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe people would have some other questions, but that is a good question.\NSo the collapse of the wave function, it's the potential becoming the actual.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.85,1:13:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And our own spiritual intention collapses it.\NAnd as we defined this morning, we're all influencing the consciousness level of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.02,1:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,hopefully in a favorable way.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.55,1:13:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My question comes from my contemplation process in\Nreleasing judgments.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.63,1:13:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And a lifelong judgment I was raised with was judgment towards wealth.\NAnd in reading the I.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.43,1:13:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Towards wealth?\NYeah, towards wealth and abundance.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.59,1:13:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People who control abundance.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.90,1:13:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good or bad about it.\NRight, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.06,1:13:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great thing, right?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.75,1:13:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great thing, right?\NYeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.01,1:13:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's good.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.03,1:13:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.26,1:14:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it as long as you feel guilty about it.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.42,1:14:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you have plenty of charity, huh?\NOkay, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.65,1:14:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, an interesting thing happened with the death of Mother Teresa.\NAnd learning about karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.73,1:14:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And parallel to that, I never really thought of the collective spirit, what its level is\Nthroughout its lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.22,1:14:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it led me into a curiosity where I began trying to calibrate karmic merit.\NAnd I don't know if any of it's accurate, but it posed really interesting questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.77,1:14:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So Mother Teresa came up at something like 240.\NAnd then Oprah came up at like 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.46,1:14:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd so that made me think of the three avatars of Buddha, Christ, and Krishna.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.61,1:14:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that Buddha had a really stunning experience in that you had said he had had many lifetimes\Nbefore and Christ had none.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.61,1:14:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought that was so interesting because Buddha gave up royalty and Buddha gave up\Nwealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.38,1:15:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems like wealth is the ultimate human challenge to differentiate or to actually\Nleave behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.57,1:15:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it gave me compassion for the wealth.\NIt gave me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.02,1:15:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And understanding that that is like a very, or my thinking was it was a very advanced\Nexperience on the earthly realm to have the karmic merit to be born into that capacity,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.34,1:15:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that ability.\NSo I just wondered if you could elaborate on karmic merit because I'm just kind of coming
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.50,1:15:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,into that knowledge through your work and its correlation to wealth.\NHe got loose and got out of the cage one time and experienced.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.40,1:16:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The life within the surrounding world and was shocked at what he discovered.\NAnd that began his research is was for the explanation for old age, sickness, suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.60,1:16:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and death and his inner research into the nature of the ego itself really has nothing\Nto do with wealth as a way of observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.60,1:16:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see wealth, you know, it's really a critical part of understanding, which we won't get\Ninto today.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.73,1:16:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The great wealth.\NThe wealth of this country, you know where it exists, you know why this is the richest
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.02,1:16:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the powerful country in the world, not because it's the evil demon, but because wealth\Ncomes from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.89,1:16:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wealth, the mind of Thomas Edison created more wealth than the total output put total\Nproduct that most of the countries on earth, just from Thomas Edison, electricity, Henry
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.75,1:17:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ford, and they had one industry after an industry after another.\NSo these industries are nothing but the consequence of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.46,1:17:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They're nothing but the consequence of creativity and along the way, you can get caught up\Nmoneyness of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.69,1:17:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think most of the creative geniuses are moneyness is irrelevant, you know, because\Nthey're so busy with the next invention.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.71,1:17:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So a whole company takes over and does that.\NSo Tesla, you know, when he died, this flat rope, no money at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.13,1:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He ended up discovering the alternating current.\NSo between Edison and Tesla and the inventor of the telephone and.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.26,1:17:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Computer chip and so America was the source of that the airport airline industry, the\Nautomobile industry, electronics, electricity, why are things like electricity that totally
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.89,1:18:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,transformed the whole planet?\NSo the capitalist, the capitalism of this country is the capitalism of creativity and
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.71,1:18:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,genius.\NOne thought of one genius is greater than the total product of all of your.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.11,1:18:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The moneyness that arises out of that is, of course, what a physical universe does with\Nit, because moneyness is the trade and barter.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.89,1:18:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's hard to trade six camels for a wife anymore when you're just ready.\NYou can write a check, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.84,1:18:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, so, so, all right.\NSo it isn't wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.85,1:18:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the attachment to wealth and the.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.65,1:19:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps ego inflation that goes with having the wealth.\NActually, wealth is very helpful if you view it as, you know, it's a time saving economy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.22,1:19:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easier to walk out the front door of the hotel and go like this and have a cab\Npull over than it is to walk all the way to the subway.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.61,1:19:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo it has certain practical advantages.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.34,1:19:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't necessary to renounce wealth.\NNow, the Buddha, because he went, went within.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.47,1:19:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw that the world as it was presented to him was not the real world.\NAnd he wanted to know what is the source of.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.39,1:19:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So that led him to the study of karma.\NKarma, and I'll just give you the understanding of it that exists here at this time, is because
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.81,1:19:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you see consciousness evolves over great eons of time, it collects onto itself learningness.\NNow, evolution does not take place in the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.02,1:19:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The physical domain is where you see the expression of creation, evolution, because\Nevolution and creation are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.27,1:20:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a quality of consciousness to evolve.\NSo the animals consciousness then plays out, plays with what it's learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.59,1:20:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't create an improved animal.\NIt doesn't create an improved grasshopper at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.50,1:20:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It munches it over on the etheric floor.\NIt doesn't create an improved grasshopper at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.13,1:20:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,plane and who's out with a new creation you don't see transitory forms in the physical domain\Nbecause the transition is on the level described by sh what is it then the level of formative
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.52,1:20:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,causation is schildrich schildrich so evolution is occurring on the level of consciousness so\Nconsciousness then has is within the non-physical domain within it consciousness evolves because
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.97,1:21:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that's its intrinsic nature you see that the emergence of life on this planet over great\Neons you just see that consciousness keeps evolving it you know up through the animal
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.25,1:21:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom on through mankind and on through the level consciousness levels of man by design\Napparently by intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.23,1:21:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of nature consciousness evolves evolves it does so on the invisible level and then\Nemerges so the potentiality becomes an actuality by virtue of intention the unmanifest becoming
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.64,1:21:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest has always been presumed to be the intention of divinity out of nothing appeared\Neverything out of the animate unmanifest appeared a universe which is infinite and
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.06,1:22:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,dimensional\Nand which grows infinitely throughout all of time and has no beginning and has no end
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.52,1:22:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which the mind cannot think of the what mind cannot comprehend it has to have a beginning\Nand end to comprehend it so foreverness and alwaysness was what the buddha began to look
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.52,1:22:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,at and he began to unravel the ego by observation the mind unraveled itself by sheer observation\Nif you're doing to watch the mind you'll see it will slowly disintegrate but the mind is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.53,1:22:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,disintegrated but just by being watched and ramada maharishi no nisargadatta maharaj\Nalways recommended that his guru told him just watch the mind that's what he did and
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.27,1:22:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,after three years of watching the mind continuously it collapsed so the buddha was on a journey\Nof uh karmic merit growth just like everyone else and had lived many lifetimes and had
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.21,1:23:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,gotten to that point of wealth and uh his uh potentiality of reaching enlightenment which\Nis so rare you're saying it's in the 0.03 or 0.04 percent less than that so apparently
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.06,1:23:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then the spirit lives on and accumulates this wisdom because that's the nature of consciousness\Nso if you segment off a personal spirit ego personal soul et cetera it partakes of the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.98,1:23:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,same quality of the nature of consciousness itself and also learns and grows over time\Nover great periods of time, great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.81,1:23:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we go in and out of body,\Nbut the spirit remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.89,1:23:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spirit is accumulating a learningness,\Na learningness over great expanses of time
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.93,1:23:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,until it becomes aware eventually\Nof the source of its own existence and its own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.93,1:23:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that challenge of giving up the palace\Nis probably one of the greatest human challenges.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.01,1:23:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it goes back to my original question,\Nis when you get to that point,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.40,1:24:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a fairly advanced state of karmic merit.\NYes, and it isn't wealth, it's the attachment to wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.28,1:24:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because wealth is just a useful tool.\NSo to Einstein or any of those people,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.67,1:24:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,wealth was just a means of doing the necessary engineering.\NSo creativity was what they're committed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.77,1:24:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the wealth of this nation is creativity itself.\NBecause it seems to be a society which potentiates, underlines,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.86,1:24:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and values individual creativity from Alexander Graham Bell to...\NGates.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.64,1:24:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Gates.\NBill Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.64,1:24:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his name?\NBill.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.18,1:24:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Bill.\NSo see, all that comes out as an automatic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.18,1:24:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you design an automobile to get you from one place to another,\Nthe world throngs to it and wants more, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.00,1:25:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My observation just comes from, like you're saying,\Ntrying to get to my own enlightenment, not so much,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.07,1:25:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to understand money and that,\NI'm trying to understand the system in which I'm observing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.84,1:25:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's as if I'm trying to gain compassion,\Nbecause I'm trying to look at everything with compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.35,1:25:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is something I used to not look at with compassion,\Nso I can see the beauty and the struggle of that challenge
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.43,1:25:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of the birthright to brilliance, like Gates, and brilliance and money,\Nand the fact that separation of money is one of the most challenging things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.47,1:25:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a writer, someone who doesn't write for money,\NI'm trying to understand the system in which I'm observing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.47,1:25:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who doesn't write for money,\Nsomeone who writes for the joy of being inside my head, inside my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.07,1:25:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Gates enjoyed computers, but there's a byproduct of that of wealth.\NAnd the byproduct of the wealth in the human experience is,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.10,1:25:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you do with all of that power and be separated from it?\NWell, I wouldn't say wealth is power, wealth is convenience.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.67,1:26:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, grace, oil on the tracks, something like that.\NSociety creates the wealth, the person doesn't create the wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.43,1:26:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how many of you know that?\NHow many automobiles did Henry Ford make?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.85,1:26:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He never made one, probably.\NHe just made the parts.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.85,1:26:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, society came in and demanded it.\NWe want this thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.85,1:26:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then society provides the workers and the incentive.\NAnd the banks, of course, you need to make money.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.85,1:26:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to create an automobile factory, you've got to make money from the banks to do it.\NSo you could look at it as mutually beneficial to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.02,1:26:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.02,1:26:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see a capitalist and a worker as a perpetrator and victim at all.\NThat was Marx's great error, disaster's error.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.52,1:26:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he separated it that way, he doesn't see that everything is mutually beneficial.\NWithout the worker, the factory can't be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.10,1:26:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the factory, there's no way to build factories.\NAnd without that, there's no capital.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.18,1:26:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that, there's no bank.\NAnd without that, there's no grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.18,1:26:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And without that, the kid's still hungry.\NI see the value in all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.18,1:27:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I see sustainability.\NI see sustainability.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.18,1:27:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I see society as mutually beneficial, a mutuality to it.\NHow you look at it, holographically.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.18,1:27:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,From this way, politics looks wrong.\NFrom this way, politics looks, how could you live without it?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.47,1:27:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,From this way, capital looks wrong.\NFrom this way, what would you wear today without the rich capitalist pigs?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.97,1:27:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou'd have to sew your own clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.97,1:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you, you'd be a busy person if it wasn't for all the rich capitalist pigs out there.\NSo, the last thing on Karmic Merit, I really enjoyed the chart that you did on the consciousness evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.97,1:27:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the things that helped me unravel layers of my unproductive programming, or productive, whichever it may be,\Nwas trying to track Karmic Merit to see the expression of that life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.97,1:27:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, I would love to know what Mother Teresa's Karmic Merit is versus Donald Trump's Karmic Merit,\Nto see where they come in and what that expression is.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.97,1:28:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's like they've de-perfected different energies within the psyche.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.97,1:28:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And it could be one can't go beyond a certain level until you've mastered it.\NSo, you've now created this world until you've mastered it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.07,1:28:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's one thing to leave the world, another thing to come back in and master both the spiritual and the physical domain.\NAnd so, I just look at, these are people who've mastered this area, this area,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.10,1:28:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe in the next lifetime, he's already done that one.\NLike, I liken it to martial art belts or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.10,1:28:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just various belts.\NCould be so.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.10,1:28:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Various signals.\NWell, you know, I see Karmic Merit as the result of the spiritual will.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.10,1:28:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, karma doesn't, you know, the scale of consciousness,\Nyou don't fluctuate up and down the scale of consciousness from moment to moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.10,1:29:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because the decision of the spiritual will seems to be the one thing that steadies the boat.\NYou know, your karma and your consciousness level doesn't go up and down with every wave.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.31,1:29:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But the intention of your, the way you set your compass, the way you set it,\Nthat's your Karmic Inherence, your Karmic Merit, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.27,1:29:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd then you learn through experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.27,1:29:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, thank you.\NThank you a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.64,1:29:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got an easier question.\NYou're describing the whole universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.03,1:29:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't count on it.\NWell, my questions have to do with the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.51,1:29:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been practicing what you teach about observing and dismantling and making a pet of the ego,\Nand I find that very liberating, and I thank you for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.82,1:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that works for me.\NBut I'm curious about the experience that you describe as the death of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.31,1:30:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whether that's a once-for-all thing that happens at a high level that most people won't experience, or what?\NYou want to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.36,1:30:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a word about that, the ego?\NI probably, if I'm honest, am imperfectionistically wanting all that there can possibly be in spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.31,1:30:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what you're doing is all that's necessary.\NIn other words, you just dismantle the ego by familiarity, by observation, by all what you learn.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.80,1:30:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that it's got a spirituality.\NI mean, the young man who was just here, at one time he was positionalized about, well, it's good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.80,1:30:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So now he sees that that was positionalizing it, and it's neither one.\NSo he transcends that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.80,1:31:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you see each barrier arise, you are willing to surrender the truth to God, to whatever you want to call it.\NSurrender it to devotion towards the evolution of your own consciousness, because that's really a way of worshiping God.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.15,1:31:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One's own potentiality is itself a worshipful act.\NThe ego then, we said it's the derivation of the evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.64,1:31:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't become really a difficulty until it acquires mind.\NIt's once mind that comes in, that now ego has a reborn, it's reborn.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.92,1:31:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal ego is reborn.\NSo the prefrontal cortex then gave it a new tool for survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.72,1:32:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when it thought it was about done there with loving dogs and cats, in came the ego, and boy, the new ball game.\NBecause the intellect now is a whole new playground.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.22,1:32:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So the four hundreds are very difficult to transcend.\NBut they are for the naive person.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.22,1:32:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But once we begin to study it and see what its nature is, it becomes just something else with the same.\NIt wants to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.22,1:32:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to control things.\NSo we see the ego does exactly the same thing as the animal did.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.27,1:32:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes competitive.\NIt wants to swell up with pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.27,1:32:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to scare others.\NAnd in the world of thinkingness, it uses thoughts as an attempt to control others.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.10,1:32:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you give it less and less worship, you begin to get dubious about the mind.\NYou begin to get...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.72,1:33:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The first step to its undoing is humility.\NTo begin to realize the limitations of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.77,1:33:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, the intellect can't get beyond 499.\NSo that's not all that impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.77,1:33:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there's people in this room that are well beyond 499.\NThey've already transcended to a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.18,1:33:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you see a thing for what it is, it loses its power over you.\NAnd then the mind and the intellect, the style of which you've already adopted,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.81,1:33:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if you just continue it as a style, then you worry about the end of the ego.\NYou don't have to worry about the end of the ego because the ego is not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.26,1:33:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What you mean is the end of the illusion of the ego as reality, which appears fearsome.\NYou know, all that I think and believe and experience and think is factual
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.93,1:34:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on something that is non-factual.\NNow, not necessarily that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.98,1:34:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like that which you've always felt is you,\Nthis very core and essence of your own being, existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.88,1:34:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,from your very first memory in life up to this very moment.\NYou see that that which you think is the very core, the essence of you,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.35,1:34:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the real, real, real you,\Nhas to be surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.18,1:34:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is where the fear comes in.\NIt's only until that moment when you think you are beyond all doubt
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.26,1:34:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is what has to be surrendered to God.\NAnd you see only that stands in your way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.26,1:34:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that happen once for all?\NHappen once for all.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.76,1:35:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning it's an event and then after that you don't have to have Fluffy anymore?\NIt's profoundly obvious that what you thought was you isn't you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.39,1:35:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how one would reawaken it.\NIt takes many years to learn how to even function in the world again
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.34,1:35:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with that peculiar phenomenon.\NBecause that which you were convinced is the core and the essence of the real you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.68,1:35:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears.\NInstead, a presence that is all-prevailing, all-knowing,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.10,1:35:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all time, etc.,\Nis the source of what the world would call happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.84,1:35:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How to remaster language and expression of a reality\Nwhich cannot really be adequately expressed in a worryingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.47,1:36:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If this does not happen, does the ego go on lifetime after lifetime?\NThat's what it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.56,1:36:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Until it finally does happen.\NYes, because death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.56,1:36:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't understand karma\Nbecause they think every time you leave the body you've died
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.64,1:36:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the end of that story.\NThat's not the end of that story at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.39,1:36:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Does the ego go on from lifetime to lifetime?\NYes, that's what we call it. That's our languaging of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.39,1:36:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That energy, you see.\NAnd the reason for that is because death is not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.40,1:36:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the very fact that death is not possible,\Nwhat happens when the body tatters over?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.56,1:36:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the law of conservation of matter,\Nthe law of conservation of energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.56,1:36:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be destroyed.\NThey can only take form.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.56,1:36:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why it dawned on mankind,\Nbut it's invidious to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.56,1:36:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the law of conservation of life.\NLife cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.56,1:37:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only transform.\NMove from one form to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.69,1:37:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And if getting reborn in a physicality as a human\Nserves its progression,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.89,1:37:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then it chooses to do so.\NI don't think it has to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.52,1:37:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an option.\NThe basic law of the universe is not only that life is not destructible,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.15,1:37:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but that all of evolution is based on free choice, free will.\NOtherwise, there's no karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.39,1:37:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're forced to be merciful or else I'll shoot you,\Nthen not too much karmic merit to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.76,1:37:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have the option to shoot the person\Nand choose otherwise, then you have karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.52,1:37:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI find all of your teachings very liberating.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.52,1:37:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I, like you, grew up with a scrupulously religious background.\NAnd this is indeed liberating.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.52,1:38:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou don't have to become an atheist to escape it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.10,1:38:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou just get the truth by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.43,1:38:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,First, thank you so much for making it okay to ask these questions,\Nbecause I never would have had the nerve to ask them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.85,1:38:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've asked you this once before.\NI asked you this a few months ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.68,1:38:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm so stuck there that I've got to ask about it again.\NI have a 32-year-old son who's struggling out there in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.14,1:38:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,having a hard time.\NHe goes up and down.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.14,1:38:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In your viewpoint.\NRight, yes, true.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.64,1:38:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going through it with your own observation\Nand the deduction and conclusion that your mind jumps in with.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.89,1:38:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's fulfilling his karmic pretension and doing exactly what he wants to.\NAnyway, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.77,1:39:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For a second, I almost saw that.\NYou see, because hitting bottom is the fastest way to God, I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.03,1:39:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,People who come in with, you know, develop addictions,\Nthey put themselves on a one-way walkway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.03,1:39:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way off.\NYou either die or you surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.97,1:39:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is the third choice.\NYou can't back it up and undo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.47,1:39:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You either surrender to God or you die of that addiction,\Nwhich means you'll come back again with the same addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.00,1:39:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and do it over and over again until the ego surrenders and says,\Nof myself, I cannot save myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.11,1:40:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, we see from brain physiology a marvelous diagram.\NThat's a factual truth of brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.96,1:40:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Until you put in spiritual intention,\Nthe left brain is unable to even come up with a suggestion
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.11,1:40:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you surrender to God.\NAnd when you say, God, I need your spiritual meeting,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.26,1:40:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly the right brain gets activated.\NYour third brain begins to emerge, and you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.26,1:40:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how could I have ever thought I could do it on my own?\NIt's obviously an impossible tool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.71,1:40:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The great revelation.\NSo hitting bottom, you can't get to hitting bottom without going there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.11,1:40:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to hit bottom from your viewpoint, see?\NRead a nice book on all about it, go to Stop Being an Enabler,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.11,1:40:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody recovers.\NIt could be this week.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.97,1:41:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be Sunday.\NSo one surrenders one's will
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.63,1:41:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to control another person's karma.\NBecause, you see, let's say enforced sobriety has no karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.39,1:41:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see guys in prison.\NIn 35 years we're killing somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.26,1:41:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,within 24 hours they already killed somebody else again.\NEnforced, forcing people to behave in a certain manner
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.27,1:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,robs them of karmic merit.\NSo what you do is pose the,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.92,1:41:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in case they've missed it somehow in our society,\Nyou pose this as an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.92,1:41:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you walk away from it.\NThe more you try to put it on them,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.92,1:41:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the more they resist.\NSo I used to have a huge practice of addiction,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.32,1:41:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, back east.\NBy the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.06,1:41:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And people would call me up and say,\Nyou know, tell me this story.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.06,1:41:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do for Joe?\NAnd they'd tell me all about Joe
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.06,1:42:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he's got fire and liver's going and all.\NYeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.06,1:42:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And what can I do for him?\NAnd I'd say, you want truth or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.06,1:42:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They all said they want truth but they lie.\NIt might possibly,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.42,1:42:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it might be possible that you're,\Nyou're asking me an honest question.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.42,1:42:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do?\NI said, buy him a case of whiskey,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.42,1:42:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,put him in a motel and leave him be.\NAnd go on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.68,1:42:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.\NThat's the truth, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.61,1:42:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy him a case of whiskey and leave him be.\NSo you leave it to the nature of the illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.68,1:42:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pathway to God.\NIt's a pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.88,1:42:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's one of the most effective pathways\Nto God on the planet today.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.43,1:42:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I think more people discovered God\Nthrough the 12 step movements
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.43,1:43:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and those self-help groups\Nthan they do through former religion anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.88,1:43:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people do you know say,\Nwell, I just discovered the so-and-so church,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.88,1:43:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, hardly ever.\NTens of millions discovered God
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.88,1:43:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through the necessity,\Neither find God or croak.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.88,1:43:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you get the message across.\NBox so related.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.64,1:43:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender or die\Nand have convulsions go insane in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.55,1:43:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is, you know,\Nyou start seeing things in the air
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.55,1:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're trying to eat you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.86,1:43:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can possibly present something as an option\Nbut not try to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.97,1:44:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You really hate this guy, don't you?\NYou're going to drive him to the real pits,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.36,1:44:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,make him suffer,\Nhelping him all the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.36,1:44:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the first step in honor?\NI don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.31,1:44:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I admitted I was powerless\Nover other people's addictions and problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.39,1:44:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and I decided to surrender my will\Nto God.
